  "text": "A method known as belief optimization is worth mentioning, as it attempts to optimize the Bethe free energy directly to a local minima, thus avoiding BPs lack of convergence guarantees [CITATION_1] . This approach is closely related to maximizing the stochastic block model likelihood directly via EM [CITATION_2] . Belief optimization is slower than BP when BP does converge, and thus is less often used in practice.",
